        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:24PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of The Knees, or 18 miles west of Fort Benton, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Benton and Carter.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
north central Montana.</instruction>
